The paper discusses channel estimation in FBMC/OQAM systems, which are a type of multicarrier communication system. This falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of preambles for channel estimation, which is a common technique in wireless communication systems and falls under the field of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple antennas for channel estimation, which falls under the field of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper compares different preamble structures via simulations, which involves statistical analysis and falls under the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
